FBIS4-3555 "drchi078_d_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 Northeast Asia XINHUA Notes Resignation of ROK Prime Minister XINHUA Notes Resignation of ROK Prime Minister OW2204100294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0948 GMT 22 Apr 94 OW2204100294 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Seoul, April 22 (XINHUA) -- South Korean Prime Minister Yi Hoe-chang handed in his resignation to President Kim Yong-sam here today, YONHAP NEWS AGENCY quoted Yi's spokesman as saying. The exact reason for Yi to resign was not immediately known. Yi, 59, former chairman of the Board of Audit and Inspection (BAI), was nominated as prime minister by President Kim to replace Hwang In-sung on December 16 of last year. Meanwhile, President Kim named Deputy Prime Minister Yi Yong-tok as his new premier today, a presidential spokesman said.
